Another flashback to 2015 and photographed @alkali_layke for an IGN interview. This was my first time being published and an unused, freshly edited, alternate photo. It was as if the universe conspired to unite us at the edge of this arid abyss, where the boundary between serendipity and destiny blurred like the horizon. Amidst the vast, sun-drenched canvas of the canyon, she emerged, a vision of vibrant contrast against the barren expanse. Clad in a playful pink two-piece adorned with 'Kirby'—a whimsical hero of her own choosing—her mysterious smile spoke volumes of secrets held in the recesses of her tattooed, pale canvas. In that moment, as her enigmatic gaze met the camera's lens, I pondered: had she stumbled upon my world, or had I, in my quest for the extraordinary, stumbled upon hers?
